# Providers Rule

## Structure

- All React context providers live in the `providers/` folder
- Each provider has its own file: `providers/{Name}Provider.tsx`
- A single `Providers` component in `providers/Providers.tsx` composes all providers for the root layout
- Export providers and hooks from `providers/index.ts`

## Conventions

- Provider components are named `{Feature}Provider` (e.g., `ToastProvider`)
- Custom hooks for consuming context are named `use{Feature}` (e.g., `useToast`)
- Keep the provider, its context, and hook in the same file for colocation
- Use `type` over `interface` for provider props and context value types
- Mark provider files with `'use client'` when they use React hooks or context

## Usage

- Import `Providers` in the root layout (or top-level client component) and wrap the app
- Import `use{Feature}` from `@/providers` in components that need the context
- Add new providers to `Providers.tsx` by nesting them in the desired order

## Example

```
providers/
  ToastProvider.tsx   # ToastProvider + useToast
  Providers.tsx      # Composes all providers
  index.ts           # Re-exports
```
